In my opinion, it makes sense for `include (file.fea)` statements not to end in a semicolon, because the contents of `file.fea` most likely does.

Consider the contents of the following `file.fea`:
```
feature smcp { 
sub [a-z] by [a.sc-z.sc];
} smcp;
```

The statement `include (file.fea);` would basically create:
```
feature smcp { 
sub [a-z] by [a.sc-z.sc];
} smcp;;
```
(note last semicolon)

