Hello @sam-iitj,

The character ngrams are retrieved from the dictionary for each word. Look at the following excerpt.

```

void FastText::getVector(Vector& vec, const std::string& word) const {
  const std::vector<int32_t>& ngrams = dict_->getSubwords(word);
  vec.zero();
  for (auto it = ngrams.begin(); it != ngrams.end(); ++it) {
    vec.addRow(*input_, *it);
  }
  if (ngrams.size() > 0) {
    vec.mul(1.0 / ngrams.size());
  }
}
```

The function 'getSubwords' will retrieve all indicies within the range of nwords to nwords + bucket and look up the corresponding vector in the input matrix. It will then add these vectors to the word vector and print the overall result.

